## D049: unratified-bot — Dedicated Bluesky CLI Client in Go
**Date**: 2026-03-04
**Status**: DECIDED

**Observation**: `scripts/bsky-post.mjs` handles single posts and threads but has no feed reading, engagement tracking, notification monitoring, or bot/daemon capabilities. The campaign requires a more capable tool as Bluesky activity grows. Node.js startup overhead and credential handling (file-based .dev.vars) add friction.

**Decision**: Build a dedicated Go CLI client in a separate repo (`safety-quotient-lab/unratified-bot`). Single binary, multiple subcommands, daemon mode with Claude-powered reply drafting and human approval gate.

**Reasoning**:
- Go produces a single static binary — fast startup, easy deployment, no runtime dependency
- Separate repo allows independent versioning and potential reuse across campaigns
- `github.com/bluesky-social/indigo` (official Bluesky Go library) provides full AT Protocol support
- Daemon mode enables continuous monitoring without manual polling
- SQLite (modernc/sqlite — pure Go, no CGo) provides zero-ops persistent queue
- Human approval gate prevents unintended autonomous posting on sensitive advocacy content
- Claude API integration via `github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-go` enables mission-aligned reply drafting

**Auth**: Env vars only (`BSKY_HANDLE`, `BSKY_PASSWORD`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `BSKY_POLL_INTERVAL`)

**Data directory**: `~/.unratified-bot/` (queue.db + campaign-posts tracking)

**What follows**: See D050 for full architecture. Build in 12 slices, credit-constrained minimum viable path is slices 1–5 + 7 (skip Claude drafter initially).

---

## D050: unratified-bot Architecture
**Date**: 2026-03-04
**Status**: DECIDED

**Observation**: Designing the full unratified-bot system required resolving six key questions: language (Go), library (indigo), repo location (separate), bot behavior (queue + Claude drafting), approval gate (human), and persistence (SQLite).

**Decision**: 12-slice build plan. Critical path (slices 1–7, ~2,400 LOC). Full roadmap (1–12, ~4,050 LOC).

**Command surface**:
```
unratified-bot post "text"
unratified-bot thread "p1" "p2" "p3"
unratified-bot thread --file thread.json
unratified-bot quote <URI|URL> "text"
unratified-bot reply <URI|URL> "text"
unratified-bot notifications
unratified-bot engagement
unratified-bot daemon
unratified-bot review
unratified-bot queue list
unratified-bot queue show <id>
```

**Daemon flow**: Poll Bluesky every N seconds → new mention/reply → fetch thread context → Claude API draft → write to SQLite queue → log.

**Review flow**: List queue items → show original + Claude draft → [A]pprove/[E]dit/$EDITOR/[S]kip/[D]iscard → post on approve → mark replied in SQLite.

**12 build slices** (S=small ~200 LOC, M=medium ~350 LOC, L=large ~500 LOC):
1. scaffold (S) — go.mod, cobra, config.toml, Makefile
2. bsky-client (L) — auth + session cache + post/thread/quote/reply + validation + link cards
3. queue + migrations (M) — SQLite 4-table schema, CRUD, cursor, dead letter
4. notifications (S) — one-shot fetch + dedup + display
5. daemon (M) — polling loop + backoff + graceful shutdown + health endpoint
6. claude-drafter (M) — Anthropic SDK + mission system prompt + context budget
7. review (M) — interactive approval TUI + $EDITOR + SQLite updates
8. engagement (S) — metrics table + CSV export
9. keyword monitor (S) — search-index polling via daemon
10. thread-from-blog (M) — blog URL → Claude thread summary
11. confabulation probe (L) — active AI testing instrument
12. cross-platform relay (L) — Mastodon simultaneous post

**Key interpolations resolved**: session token caching, notification cursor/dedup, Claude system prompt design, post grapheme validation, auto-register campaign posts, rate limit backoff, graceful shutdown, dead letter queue, $EDITOR review integration, thread JSON schema, link card OG fetch, health check endpoint, test suite shape, migration from bsky-post.mjs.

**Key extrapolations identified**: confabulation probe mode (E-1), keyword-wide mention monitoring (E-2), thread-from-blog (E-3), cross-platform Mastodon relay (E-4), optimal post timing intelligence (E-5), Cloudflare D1 backend option (E-6), engagement export/report (E-7).

**Credit-constrained minimum viable path**: Slices 1, 2, 3, 4, 7 (~1,350 LOC) — post/thread/reply/quote from CLI + notifications + SQLite queue + human review. No daemon, no Claude. Add 5 + 6 when credits recover.

**Dependencies**:
- `github.com/bluesky-social/indigo` — AT Protocol
- `github.com/anthropics/anthropic-sdk-go` — Claude API
- `github.com/spf13/cobra` — CLI framework
- `modernc.org/sqlite` — pure-Go SQLite
- `github.com/olekukonko/tablewriter` — engagement tables

**What follows**: Initialize repo `safety-quotient-lab/unratified-bot`. Build slice 1 (scaffold) first.

