## D051: TOC + Deep-Link Anchors Across All MDX Content Pages
**Date**: 2026-03-05
**Status**: DECIDED + IMPLEMENTED

**Observation**: No heading `id` attributes existed on any MDX-rendered pages, making it impossible to deep-link to specific sections (educator template letters, ICESCR article subsections, etc.). HN UX constraints already documented this as a MEDIUM priority need. The educator template letter was the triggering use case — no way to share a direct link to it.

**Decision**: Add `rehype-slug` + `rehype-autolink-headings` to astro.config.mjs (applied to both .md and .mdx via shared `rehypePlugins` array), create `TableOfContents.svelte` island, wire TOC into all content slug page templates.

**Reasoning**:
- rehype-slug auto-generates stable `id` attributes from heading text at build time — zero per-file MDX changes required
- rehype-autolink-headings appends a `#` anchor link to every heading — hover-reveal pattern keeps UI clean
- Astro's `render()` API returns a `headings` array (`[{depth, slug, text}]`) usable at build time for TOC generation
- `<details open>` pattern for TOC: collapses on mobile, open by default on desktop, no JS layout dependency
- Heading text drives the slug — stable heading names = stable URLs; renamed template-letters headings NOW before promoting deep links publicly

**Pages affected**: action/[...slug], gap/[...slug], connection/[...slug], evidence/[...slug], covenant/articles/[...slug] (via ArticleLayout)

**Deep link examples now functional**:
- `unratified.org/action/template-letters#educator-letter`
- `unratified.org/action/template-letters#general-letter`
- `unratified.org/action/template-letters#healthcare-letter`
- `unratified.org/action/template-letters#education-letter`
- `unratified.org/action/template-letters#economic-impact-letter`

**What follows**: Promote deep links in social copy (Bluesky templates), educator outreach emails, and any future reply template guidance.

