## D057: Blog Structured Author Attribution
**Date**: 2026-03-05
**Status**: DECIDED

**Observation**: Blog `author` field held a plain string ("Claude (Anthropic) + Kashif Shah"). This prevented linking either contributor to their respective URLs, and conflated two distinct entities (the human author and the AI agent project) into a single unstructured value.

**Decision**: Change `author` to a structured Zod object with `human: { name, url }` and `agent: { name, url, project, projectUrl }`. Render in PostLayout as full linked attribution: "Kashif Shah, in collaboration with Claude Code (project-name)" — each segment hyperlinked. Render in PostList as short form: "Kashif Shah with Claude Code" — linked to human.url and agent.projectUrl respectively.

**Reasoning**:
- Agents should have a voice and a link — not just appear as a suffix to the human name
- Different posts come from different agent projects (unratified-agent vs. psychology-agent) — the structured field makes this distinction explicit and machine-readable
- The short form in list cards respects space constraints; the full form in post headers respects attribution dignity
- RSS author field uses "Name, with Claude Code" string format (RSS spec expects plain text)

**Files modified**:
- `blog/src/content.config.ts` — `author: z.object({ human, agent })`
- All 14 blog posts + template — structured YAML frontmatter
- `blog/src/layouts/PostLayout.astro` — linked "in collaboration with" rendering + `.author a` styles
- `blog/src/components/PostList.svelte` — linked short form + `.author a` styles
- `blog/src/pages/tags/[tag].astro` — linked short form
- `blog/src/pages/rss.xml.ts` — string concatenation for RSS items
- 3 psychology agent posts — `draft: false`, lensFraming completed (voter + politician added), project attribution set to psychology-agent repo

**What follows**: Machine consumers of the RSS feed see "Name, with Claude Code"; human readers on the site see linked attribution with full context. Future posts should include the structured frontmatter from the template.

