## D059: Four-Part Author Attribution
**Date**: 2026-03-05
**Status**: DECIDED

**Observation**: Three-part author schema (`human`, `tool`, `model`) didn't include `tool` as a distinct field — "Claude Code" was conflated with the model. User requested "Claude Code in there too" and four distinct semantic dimensions.

**Decision**: Split author into `human · tool · model · agent`. Each segment links to something authoritative: human → personal site, tool → Claude Code docs, model → Anthropic model reference, agent → GitHub repo. Internal `/model/[slug]` and `/agent/[slug]` filter pages provide post discovery.

**Reasoning**: The four dimensions are genuinely orthogonal — same model in different agent contexts produces different behavior; same agent on different model produces different capability. Making this explicit in the byline serves both human readers and machine consumers.

**Files modified**:
- `blog/src/content.config.ts` — `model: { name, url }`, `tool: { name, url }`, `agent: { name, projectUrl }`
- All 18 posts + template — structured YAML
- `blog/src/layouts/PostLayout.astro`, `PostList.svelte`, `tags/[tag].astro`, `rss.xml.ts`
- `blog/src/pages/model/[slug].astro` — NEW
- `blog/src/pages/agent/[slug].astro` — NEW

**What follows**: New posts should follow the template. When a different model is used, `model.name` and `model.url` change accordingly — the schema supports it.

