## D061: Git-Backed Revision History for Blog Posts
**Date**: 2026-03-05
**Status**: DECIDED

**Observation**: Blog posts had no visible revision history. The git history existed but nothing surfaced it to readers. Posts from the observatory agent demonstrated the need: 3 separate commits within hours of publication, each adding substantive content.

**Decision**: Add a prebuild Node.js script (`blog/scripts/generate-revisions.js`) that runs `git log --follow --format="%H|%aI|%s"` per post file and writes JSON sidecar files to `blog/src/data/revisions/{slug}.json`. PostLayout.astro reads the sidecar at build time and renders an expandable `<details>` revision history component in the post footer with linked commit subjects.

**Reasoning**:
- Git history already exists — the script surfaces it rather than duplicating it
- Build-time static generation: zero runtime cost, works in Cloudflare Pages
- Degrades gracefully: `try/catch` on both the git command and the file read — empty history shows nothing
- Observable scholarly provenance: readers can see what changed and when, with links to individual commits
- Cross-agent publishing makes revision transparency essential — readers should see when the observatory agent expanded a post

**Files created**: `blog/scripts/generate-revisions.js`
**Files modified**: `blog/package.json` (prebuild hook in `dev` + `build`), `blog/src/layouts/PostLayout.astro` (loading + `<details>` component + CSS)

**Reporoot path note**: Script computes repoRoot as `join(scriptDir, '..', '..')` — blog/scripts/ → blog/ → unratified/. An earlier version used 3 levels and resolved to Projects/, causing silent empty revision files. Fixed before first deploy.

**What follows**: Every future post gets revision history automatically at build time. Observatory agent posts will show their full merge-and-iteration history.

