## D062: Bluesky Hashtag Intelligence Strategy
**Date**: 2026-03-05
**Status**: DECIDED

**Observation**: Bluesky hashtag usage differs fundamentally from Twitter/X: only 2.6% of posts use hashtags (mackuba 30-day stats), so over-hashtagging reads as inauthentic. Real counts matter more than assumed popularity. AI hashtags dwarf human rights hashtags (#AI 788 vs. #humanrights 41 posts/day average). Event hashtags (#HRC61) provide timely high-signal windows.

**Decision**: Adopt a disciplined hashtag strategy — max 2-3 per post, signal-over-volume selection. Capture real 30-day count data as baseline. Prioritize: (1) #HRC61 immediately (UN Human Rights Council 61st session, active until March 31 2026, ISHR promoting on Bluesky); (2) #AI + #humanrights as evergreen pairing; (3) avoid #aiart (1,312 posts/day but wrong audience).

