## D065: @unratified.org Domain Handle on Bluesky
**Date**: 2026-03-06
**Status**: DECIDED

**Observation**: @unratified.bsky.social is the default handle. Custom domain handles (e.g. @unratified.org) verify identity and increase trust, as the domain itself serves as the DID verification endpoint.

**Decision**: Update Bluesky handle to @unratified.org via DNS TXT record at `_atproto.unratified.org` → `did=did:plc:dj5bft77jjjfbk7xkvon5bpk`, then call `agent.com.atproto.identity.updateHandle`.

**Reasoning**: Domain handle = verified identity. Profile now reads @unratified.org which matches the website, strengthens brand coherence, and makes the account harder to impersonate. DNS TXT verification is the canonical AT Protocol method. Script `bsky-update-handle.mjs` handles DNS pre-check + update atomically.

**What follows**: BSKY_HANDLE in .dev.vars updated to `unratified.org`. All CLI scripts authenticate correctly. Profile visible at https://bsky.app/profile/unratified.org.

