## D068: unratified-bot Go CLI — Slices 1+3+4+7
**Date**: 2026-03-06
**Status**: DECIDED + IMPLEMENTED

**Observation**: Bluesky outreach for the campaign required manual posting and had no visibility into notifications (mentions, replies, likes). The JS scripts (`bsky-post.mjs`, `bsky-post-queue.mjs`) handle posting but not queue management or notification review.

**Decision**: Build a Go CLI (`unratified-bot`) with four slices: scaffold (cobra + config.toml), SQLite queue (4-table schema: posts/cursors/seen_notifications/metrics), one-shot notification fetcher, and interactive bubbletea review TUI. No Claude API cost. Deferred: daemon (S5), claude-drafter (S6), engagement metrics (S8), confabulation probe (S11), cross-platform relay (S12).

**Reasoning**: Go produces a single static binary. `modernc.org/sqlite` eliminates CGO/gcc dependency. bubbletea provides a mature TUI framework. The review TUI (approve/edit in $EDITOR/discard) delivers the key value: a human review gate before anything goes live. Slices 2/5/6 deferred because hand-rolled XRPC client in `internal/bsky/client.go` covers the needed endpoints without a full SDK.

**Files**: `main.go`, `cmd/{root,notify,queue,review}.go`, `internal/{config,bsky,db}/*.go`, `Makefile`, `config.toml.example` — committed e1d2aa9 in `safety-quotient-lab/unratified-bot`.

**What follows**: Bot usable immediately. Queue posts with `./bot queue add "text"`, run `./bot review` to approve/post interactively, `./bot notify` to check mentions. Posts 11–18 can flow through this queue.

