## D071: Targeted Thread Engagement Pattern
**Date**: 2026-03-06
**Status**: DECIDED + PRACTISED

**Observation**: First organic reply came from @triall.ai ("ai moving faster than anyone can build guardrails"). Separately, a thread about democratic apathy contained @knightingael's claim that "the U.S. has laws to stand up to corrupt government" — an implicit assumption that civil rights = sufficient rights protection.

**Decision**: Reply to specific claims within threads rather than broadcasting to the original post. Target the most precise entry point where ICESCR adds something the conversation lacks.

**Reasoning**: @knightingael made a factually incomplete claim (civil protections ≠ economic rights). Replying there adds genuine value and draws a substantive interlocutor into the conversation. Replying to the original post would read as self-promotion into a grief thread.

**What follows**: Standing pattern — `./bot view <url>` to read thread, identify sharpest entry point, draft with specific mention, `./bot reply <uri> "text"`.

