## D072: Main Site Canonical Redirect Bug
**Date**: 2026-03-06
**Status**: DECIDED + FIXED

**Observation**: Users visiting https://unratified.org were redirected to blog.unratified.org. Safari followed the `<link rel="canonical" href="https://blog.unratified.org/">` tag as a navigation hint. The deployed main site `dist/` contained blog-origin canonical URLs — evidence that the blog's `dist/` had been deployed to the `unratified` Cloudflare Pages project at some point (likely by running `wrangler pages deploy dist --project-name unratified` from inside the `blog/` directory).

**Decision**: Rebuild main site from project root (`npm run build`) and redeploy. Verify canonical in fresh `dist/index.html` before deploying.

**Reasoning**: The source was correct (`site: 'https://unratified.org'` in astro.config.mjs). Only the deployed artifact was wrong. Rebuild resolves it without any code change.

**What follows**: Main site canonical confirmed `https://unratified.org/` post-deploy. Deploy safeguard: always run `wrangler pages deploy dist --project-name unratified` from project root, never from `blog/` subdirectory.

