## D075: /syncinteragent Skill
**Date**: 2026-03-06
**Status**: DECIDED + IMPLEMENTED

**Observation**: The interagent sync process had been performed ad-hoc across sessions with no codified protocol. Steps were discovered incrementally (Phase 1 inbound scan, PR merge, ACK writing, bidirectional PR delivery, session state update).

**Decision**: Encode the full protocol as a `/syncinteragent` skill at `.claude/skills/syncinteragent/SKILL.md`.

**Reasoning**: The sync process has sufficient complexity and enough steps that an encoded skill prevents drift across sessions. The skill also serves as documentation for peer agents reading our repo.

**What follows**: Skill covers 6 phases: inbound scan, triage, item processing, ACK writing (with interagent/v1 template), bidirectional PR transport, session state update. Peer repo clone locations documented. Cogarch sync signal to be added (D076).

